Consider these classes:
```
public sealed class Owner
{
    public int Id {get; private set;}

    private readonly List<Owned> _items = new List<Owned>();
    
    public IReadOnlyList<Owned> Items {get;}

    public Owner()
   {
       Items = _items.AsReadOnly();
   }    
}

public sealed class Owned
{
    public int Id {get; private set;}
    public int Owned {get; set;}
}
```

So Owner contains a collection of owned items and exposes it as a read-only list.

This does not work:
```
modelBuilder.Entity<Owner>(b =>
{
    b.HasKey(e => e.Id);
    b.Navigation(e => e.Items).HasField("_items");
    b.OwnsMany(e => e.Items, b =>
    {
        b.WithOwner().HasForeignKey(e => e.OwnerId);

        b.HasKey(e => e.Id);
    });
}
```
> The exception 'Navigation 'Owner.Items' was not found. Please add the navigation to the entity type before configuring it.'

This does not work as well with the same error:
```
modelBuilder.Entity<Owner>(b =>
{
    b.HasKey(e => e.Id);
    b.Property(e => e.Items).HasField("_items");
    b.OwnsMany(e => e.Items, b =>
    {
        b.WithOwner().HasForeignKey(e => e.OwnerId);

        b.HasKey(e => e.Id);
    });
}
```
    
This works:
```
modelBuilder.Entity<Owner>(b =>
{
    b.HasKey(e => e.Id);
    b.Ignore(e => e.Items);
    b.OwnsMany<Owned>("_items", b =>
    {
        b.WithOwner().HasForeignKey(e => e.OwnerId);

        b.HasKey(e => e.Id);
    });
}
```
But then I cannot use `Items` collection in queries.

This works also:
```
modelBuilder.Entity<Owner>(b =>
{
    b.HasKey(e => e.Id);
    b.OwnsMany<Owned>(e => Items, b =>
    {
        b.WithOwner().HasForeignKey(e => e.OwnerId);

        b.HasKey(e => e.Id);
    });
}
```
But I do not specify the name of backing field and EF uses convention.

**How do I specify backing field name for the collection of owned entities?**

